sentences: Vincent de Moor (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈvɪnsɛnt də ˈmoːr]; born 1973, Delft, Netherlands) is a Dutch trance artist.
He is most notable for his work with the record producer Ferry Corsten under the working title, "Veracocha," and for his 2001 single, "Fly Away".
De Moor first recorded in 1993 as Fix To Fax.
The track was first released in 1996, and reached peaked in the UK Singles Chart at #54 in August 1997.

The track featured on De Moor's second album Moor (2000), along with the singles "Shamu", "Between 2 Fires" and "Eternity (Forever)".
